\q2
\v 12 and kindness, Lord, to thee;
\q every man thou rewardest
\q2 for whatever he has done.

\c 63
\d A song of David, when he was in the desert of Judah.
\q
\v 1 O God, thou art my God, I yearn for thee;
\q body and soul, I thirst, I long for thee,
\q like a land without water, weary, dry.
\b
\q
\v 2 I have seen thee in the sanctuary,
\q2 with visions of thy power and majesty,
\q
\v 4 so will I bless thee while I live,
\q2 lifting my hands in prayer to thee.
\b
\q
\v 3 Thy love is more than life to me;
\q2 so my lips praise thee.
\q
\v 5 My soul is richly fed,
\q2 and with glad lips I sing thy praise.
\b
\q
\v 6 When I remember thee in bed,
\q2 and muse on thee by night,
\q
\v 8 my soul clings close to thee,
\q2 thy right hand holds me fast;
\q
\v 7 for thou hast been my help,
\q2 and shadowed by thy wings I sing.
