\q
\v 9 Those who would take my life shall be destroyed,
\q2 they shall go down to death,
\q
\v 10 flung to the sword,
\q2 left as a prey for jackals.
\q
\v 11 But the king shall rejoice in God,
\q2 and all the loyal shall exult
\q2 [[for false rebels shall be silenced]].

\c 64
\d From the Choirmaster’s collection. A song of David.
\q
\v 1 List to my plaint, O God,
\q2 save me from the foe and his terrors,
\q
\v 2 hide me from villains and their plots,
\q2 from gangs of evildoers,
\q
\v 3 whetting their tongue like a sword,
\q2 and aiming bitter words like arrows,
