\q
\v 7 But God shoots at them with his arrow,
\q2 wounding them suddenly;
\q
\v 8 he trips them up in their own plot,
\q2 till all who see them recoil in horror.
\q
\v 9 So all men, noting the deeds of God,
\q2 shall tell of what he does;
\q
\v 10 good men will rejoice in the Eternal,
\q2 and shelter beside him;
\q2 right-minded men will all exult.

\c 65
\d From the Choirmaster’s collection. A song of David, for music.
\q
\v 1 ’Tis fitting to praise thee in Sion, O God;
\q2 in Jerusalem shall vows be paid to thee.
\q
\v 2 O thou who hearest prayer,
\q2 all men shall come to thee.
\q
\v 3 Though our sins be too much for us,
\q2 ’tis thine to cancel our transgressions.
\q
\v 4 Happy is he whom thus thou choosest
\q2 to dwell in thy courts, close to thee.
\q Fain would we have our fill of this,
\q2 thy house, thy sacred shrine—its bliss.
\b
\q
\v 5 God of our victory, answering our prayers
\q2 with deeds of dread, so loyally,
