\q
\v 24 Behold God entering the sanctuary,
\q2 my God, my King, in high procession,
\q
\v 25 singers in front, musicians behind,
\q2 between them girls with tambourines,
\q
\v 26 singing, “Bless the Lord God in your choirs,
\q2 O Israel’s offspring!”
\q
\v 27 In front the Benjamites, so few,
\q2 the chiefs of Judah, a great company,
\q2 the chiefs of Zebulun and Naphtali!
