\q
\v 29 From thy temple high above Jerusalem,
\q2
\v 28 display thy strength, O God,
\q who has so mightily prevailed for us;
\q2
\v 29b there kings must offer thee tribute.
\q
\v 30 Check that Brute of a Nile-power,
\q2 the bullocks and steers of pagans,
\q trample down crafty pollicy,
\q2 rout all the races that rejoice in war,
\q
\v 31 till even Egypt sends ambassadors,
\q2 and Ethiopia hurries to submit to God.
