\q
\v 32 Sing to God, O kingdoms of the world,
\q2 oh celebrate the Lord!
\q
\v 33 Praise him who rides high on the ancient heavens,
\q2 whose voice thunders aloud.
\q
\v 34 Praise God for his might,
\q2 whose sovereign sway is over Israel,
\q2 whose might is in the skies.
\q
\v 35 God strikes awe from his sanctuary,
\q2 the God of Israel who bestows
\q2 prowess and power on people blessed by God.

\c 69
\d From the Choirmaster’s collection. To the tune of “The Lilies.” A song of David.
\q
\v 1 Save me, O God,
\q2 for the waters are threatening my life;
\q
\v 2 I am sinking deep in the mud,
\q2 where foothold there is none,
\q I have fallen into waters deep,
\q2 floods o’er me sweep.
\q
\v 3 I am wearied with crying,
\q2 my throat is parched,
\q mine eyes are weak
