\v 11 when I clothed myself in sackcloth,
\q2 I became their byword;
\q
\v 12 men make a jest of me in public,
\q2 they put me into their maudlin songs.
\q
\v 13 But as for me, I pray to thee;
\q2 in thy great generosity,
\q3 O God, do thou accept me;
\q2 answer me with thy loyal aid,
\q
\v 14 save me from sinking in the mud,
\q2 from the deep waters of hatred,
\q
\v 15 let not the flood sweep over me,
\q2 let not the depths drown me;
\q2 let not death close over me.
\q
\v 16 Answer me, O Eternal, in thy love,
\q2 in thy vast pity turn to me;
\q
\v 17 hide not thy face from thy servant,
\q2 answer me quickly, for I am in misery;
\q
\v 18 come to me, rescue my life,
\q2 set me in safety from my foes.
\q
\v 19 Thou knowest how I am taunted,
\q2 my foes are plain to thee;
\q
\v 20 their taunts have broken my heart,
\q2 I am sick to the soul;
