\q
\v 4 He fixes the number of the stars,
\q2 and gives a name to each.
\q
\v 5 Great is our Lord, mighty in power,
\q2 his wisdom is unsearchable.
\q
\v 6 The Eternal has relief for the afflicted,
\q2 he brings the ungodly to the ground.
\b
\q
\v 7 Sing thanks to the Eternal,
\q2 make melody to our God upon the lyre,
\q
\v 8 who covers the sky with clouds,
\q2 provides rain for the earth,
\q till grass grows on the very hills,
\q2 and fodder for the beasts that serve mankind,
\q
\v 9 who gives wild animals their food,
\q2 that cry for it at eventide.
\q
\v 10 He cares not for the strength of the war-horse,
\q2 delights not in man’s armour;
\q
\v 11 the Eternal delights in those who revere him,
\q2 who trust to his own goodness.
